The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for semantic relation extraction and classification in scientific papers. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they cover the use of machine learning algorithms for NLP tasks. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as it deals with the extraction of information from text. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still relevant as it covers the use of neural networks for various tasks.
